The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                A 22-year-old law student and his mother allegedly killed themselves by consuming poison late on Monday in Khardah. Police said Rajdeep Chakraborty was depressed as he was unable to repay loans taken from friends. His mother Bandana killed herself after realising that he had consumed poison, the police said. Neighbours took them to hospitals, where they died . No suicide note was found.     The screening of Bengali film Poran Jai Joliya Re, which was stayed by the high court on Monday, can continue till the appeal against the order is disposed of. The lawyers of Hindi film-maker Vipul Shah, who had moved court accusing Poran Jai of infringing the copyright of his 2007 film Namastey London, told a high court division bench on Tuesday that their client wouldnt move a contempt case against the makers of the Bengali film till the appeal was disposed of. Poran Jai producers Shree Venkatesh Films had challenged Mondays stay order before the division bench. The case will come up for hearing again on Wednesday.    Security has been stepped up in Sector V after the Centre issued a terror alert for Independence Day. Vehicles are being checked at strategic points in the tech hub, said Debabrata Das, the additional superintendent of North 24-Parganas police. Mobile vans will keep vigil in the township, said an officer. S.A. Ahmed, the chairman of Nabadiganta Industrial Township Authority, said six closed-circuit TV cameras have been installed.                                                                                                                                                                
